<subSubSection id="C359FCF8FFCEFFEFFF549DE3FB590648" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFCAF73FFCEFFEFFF549DE3FB590648" blockId="4.[136,1452,911,1082]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis id="B9377361FFCEFFEFFF549DE3FF2801DB" bold="true" box="[136,210,912,938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C43D4F0FFCEFFEFFF019DE3FE4C01D8" box="[221,438,911,938]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cassia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="semifalcata">
<emphasis id="B9377361FFCEFFEFFF019DE3FE4C01D8" box="[221,438,911,938]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Cassia semifalcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed as a new species by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2D282FFCEFFEFFCBE9DFCFBB101DB" author="Vellozo, J. M. C." box="[866,1099,911,938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" refId="ref6168" refString="Vellozo, J. M. C. (1829) Florae fluminensis, seu, Descriptionum plantarum praefectura Fluminensi sponte mascentium liber primus ad systema sexuale concinnatus. Typographia nationali, Flumine Januario. 352 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 745" type="book" year="1829">Vellozo (1829: 167)</bibRefCitation>
without any indication of the 
<typeStatus id="54F811D1FFCEFFEFFF549DC0FF1401BC" box="[136,238,947,973]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">holotype</typeStatus>
. As such, and following the recommendations of articles 9.11 and 9.12 of the ICNB (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2D282FFCEFFEFFB639DC0FA6501BF" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Marhold, D. - Z. Li. K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[1215,1439,947,974]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" refId="ref5959" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Marhold, D. - Z. Li. K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017." type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="B9377361FFCEFFEFFAFD9DC7FAA101BC" box="[1313,1371,947,973]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
), we are designating the illustration presented by Vellozo tab. 68, in Fl. Flumin., T. 4, 1831[“1827”]) as the 
<typeStatus id="54F811D1FFCEFFEFFAFB9DA4FA740180" box="[1319,1422,983,1009]" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C43D4F0FFCEFFEFFF549D8FFEA60664" box="[136,348,1019,1046]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cassia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="190" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="semifalcata">
<emphasis id="B9377361FFCEFFEFFF549D8FFEA60664" box="[136,348,1019,1046]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="190">Cassia semifalcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as that illustration contemplates all of the characters presented in the protologue, no type material was referred to in the original description, and no specimen used by Vellozo has been located.
</paragraph>
